<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="414" pageId="4" pageNumber="413" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1951,2013]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="414" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1951,1976]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pygofer short, approximately quadrangular, with bifurcate apical lobe and microsetae on apex and ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[335,468,1988,2013]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">
Figs 17 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[423,437,1988,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">–</emphasis>
18
</figureCitation>
). Style with strong basal curvature, with thin apex ventrally curved, lateral margins smooth, microsetae only on apical portion (
<figureCitation box="[657,790,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">
Figs 20 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[745,759,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">–</emphasis>
21
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus enlarged, with two pairs of apical long and slender processes (
<figureCitation box="[361,492,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">
Figs 22 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[445,459,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">–</emphasis>
24
</figureCitation>
). Anal tube with pair of short processes with rounded apices (
<figureCitation box="[1183,1312,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">
Figs 17 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1267,1281,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">–</emphasis>
18
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
